This is the best and easiest rack of lamb recipe I've tried. A full tablespoon of garlic is a lot, though - the first time I made it the garlic didn't cook all the way through, and there was a slightly harsh raw garlic taste. I cut back just a bit now, to about 2 teaspoons or three regular sized cloves. Its really plenty.

