Rating: 3
This was truly delicious! I had some lovely lamb striploins (rather than racks) so used this recipe as a starting point with a few modifications. I generously sprinkled lamb with coarse sea salt and fresh ground pepper then quickly seared in olive oil over high heat to seal in the juices. I used a combo of Dijon and whole grain mustard, added fresh rosemary as well as thyme, and whisked in an egg yolk which helped the crumb coating to adhere. Rather than toast the breadcrumbs, I melted 2 tbsp. butter and stirred into the crumbs prior to coating the lamb - the crust browned/crisped nicely while roasting. I baked at 400 degrees (my oven runs a little hot) for 20 min. and the lamb was perfectly done (medium-rare) after tenting/resting for 10 minutes before slicing. Very moist, tender and flavourful, this lamb was a gastronomic delight!

