This very close to a favourite recipe I had lost. I use ground toasted hazelnuts instead of breadcrumbs. Also I use mixed herbs vs. only thyme. Added a rich red currant meat-based gravy with a touch of mint...heaven. No one knew I lost my original recipe. It's important to know that in racks of lamb...the ribs/meat will vary in size per your source. Little ribs are preferred, hence the 15-10 min cooking times you tend to see. For a Welsh treat..make munchep... a blend of mashed potatoes, parsnips, carrots & parsley.

